# Prettier Conformance

All code MUST conform to Prettier on first write.

## Effective Config (defaults + .prettierrc overrides)

| Option | Value |
|---|---|
| printWidth | **80** |
| tabWidth | **2** |
| useTabs | **false** (spaces only) |
| semi | **false** (no semicolons) |
| singleQuote | **true** |
| trailingComma | **"all"** |
| bracketSpacing | **true** (`{ a }` not `{a}`) |
| arrowParens | **"always"** (`(x) =>` not `x =>`) |
| endOfLine | **"lf"** |
| quoteProps | **"as-needed"** |
| jsxSingleQuote | **false** |
| bracketSameLine | **false** |
| singleAttributePerLine | **false** |

## Line Width

Lines MUST NOT exceed 80 characters. Break arguments
onto separate lines when needed:

```typescript
// BAD — over 80 chars
await this.service.method(firstArg, secondArg, thirdArg)

// GOOD
await this.service.method(
  firstArg,
  secondArg,
  thirdArg,
)
```

## Checklist Before Every Line

1. Under 80 characters
2. Single quotes, no semicolons
3. Trailing commas on multi-line structures
4. 2-space indentation, no tabs
5. Spaces inside braces: `{ a }` not `{a}`
6. Parens on single arrow params: `(x) =>` not `x =>`
